            <h1 class="section__header">Gym Workouts at FIT-TRACK</h1>
            <p class="section__description">
                Build strength and muscle with our comprehensive gym workouts. Our experienced trainers will help you achieve your fitness goals with personalized routines.
            </p>

            <div class="gym-exercises">
                <h2>Types of Gym Exercises</h2>
                <p>At FIT-TRACK, we offer a variety of gym workouts to cater to different fitness levels:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Weightlifting:</strong> Build muscle and strength with free weights and machines.</li>
                    <li><strong>Bodyweight Training:</strong> Use your body weight for resistance exercises.</li>
                    <li><strong>Cardio Machines:</strong> Improve endurance with treadmills, ellipticals, and bikes.</li>
                    <li><strong>Functional Training:</strong> Enhance everyday movements with functional exercises.</li>
                    <li><strong>Group Classes:</strong> Join our classes for a fun and motivating workout experience.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="gym-benefits">
                <h2>Benefits of Gym Workouts</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Increases muscle strength and endurance</li>
                    <li>Improves overall fitness and health</li>
                    <li>Boosts metabolism and aids in weight management</li>
                    <li>Enhances mental health and mood</li>
                    <li>Provides a structured environment for workouts</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="gym-exercises-list">
                <h2>Basic Gym Exercises</h2>

                <div class="gym-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/GYM/Squats.avif" alt="Squats">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>1. Squats</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Stand with feet shoulder-width apart.<br>
                            Lower your body as if sitting back into a chair, keeping your chest up.<br>
                            Return to standing position and repeat.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens legs, glutes, and core; improves balance and flexibility.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="gym-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/GYM/Bench press.webp" alt="Bench Press">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>2. Bench Press</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Lie on a bench with feet flat on the ground.<br>
                            Grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width.<br>
                            Lower the bar to your chest and press it back up.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Builds upper body strength, particularly in the chest, shoulders, and triceps.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="gym-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/GYM/Deadlift.webp" alt="Deadlifts">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>3. Deadlifts</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Stand with feet hip-width apart, barbell in front.<br>
                            Bend at the hips and knees to grip the bar.<br>
                            Lift the bar by extending your hips and knees until standing.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens the back, glutes, and hamstrings; improves posture.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="gym-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/GYM/lunges.webp" alt="Lunges">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>4. Lunges</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Stand tall and step forward with one leg.<br>
                            Lower your hips until both knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.<br>
                            Push back to the starting position and switch legs.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens legs and glutes; improves balance and coordination.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="gym-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/GYM/pull ups.jpg" alt="Pull-Ups">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>5. Pull-Ups</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Hang from a pull-up bar with palms facing away.<br>
                            Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar.<br>
                            Lower back down and repeat.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens the back, shoulders, and arms; improves grip strength.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="gym-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/GYM/plank.jpg" alt="Plank">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>6. Plank</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Start in a push-up position with elbows under shoulders.<br>
                            Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels.<br>
                            Hold the position for as long as possible.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens core, shoulders, and back; improves stability.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="gym-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/GYM/bicep curls.jpg" alt="Bicep Curls">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>7. Bicep Curls</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, arms at your sides.<br>
                            Curl the weights up towards your shoulders, keeping elbows close to your body.<br>
                            Lower back down and repeat.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens biceps; improves arm definition.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="gym-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/GYM/tricep dips.jpg" alt="Tricep Dips">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>8. Tricep Dips</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Sit on the edge of a bench with hands beside you.<br>
                            Slide off the bench and lower your body by bending your elbows.<br>
                            Push back up to the starting position.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens triceps; improves upper body strength.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="gym-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/GYM/leg press.jpg" alt="Leg Press">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>9. Leg Press</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Sit on a leg press machine with feet on the platform.<br>
                            Push the platform away by extending your legs.<br>
                            Slowly return to the starting position.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens legs and glutes; isolates lower body muscles.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="gym-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/GYM/shoulder press.jpg" alt="Shoulder Press">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>10. Shoulder Press</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Stand or sit with a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height.<br>
                            Press the weights overhead until arms are fully extended.<br>
                            Lower back to shoulder height and repeat.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Strengthens shoulders and triceps; improves upper body strength.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

